<collectingCountry id="4BE861EA400C5F27FD41F8B64C623F30" box="[691,774,1852,1874]" name="Mexico" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, where it was collected, Cerro Boquerón.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A400C5F27FCC8FF4F4C983A86" blockId="27.[826,1443,196,740]" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FCC8FF4F4C9938B8" box="[826,1021,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
Adult similar to other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FAF8FF4E4AC638BB" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1290,1442,196,217]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FAF8FF4E4AC638BB" box="[1290,1442,196,217]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group species. In the adult the main differences are in the face, with a vague central vitta, which is also present in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FC30FEAB4B313954" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[962,1109,289,310]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamorum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FC30FEAB4B313954" box="[962,1109,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">C. mamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FB48FEAA4A363957" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1210,1362,288,309]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FB48FEAA4A363957" box="[1210,1362,288,309]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group species have a clear and distinct black central vitta. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FCC8FED44C943911" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,1008,350,371]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FCC8FED44C943911" box="[826,1008,350,371]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">C. boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FB60FED44A413911" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1170,1317,350,371]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamorum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FB60FED44A413911" box="[1170,1317,350,371]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">C. mamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having black, not yellow, hairs on the face, mesonotum without vittae, and black-haired tergites 3 and 4. The larva is very similar to other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FBA9FE304B9739AD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1115,1267,442,463]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FBA9FE304B9739AD" box="[1115,1267,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group species. The main difference is in the posterior breathing tube that is punctate above the transverse ridge, and wider than the width of the pupal spiracles. The posterior breathing tube is also punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FB4CFDBF4A363A28" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1214,1362,565,586]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamorum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FB4CFDBF4A363A28" box="[1214,1362,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">C. mamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in that species it is narrower, only about as wide as the pupal spiracles. The posterior breathing tube is also short in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FC6BFD1A4B553AC7" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[921,1073,656,677]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FC6BFD1A4B553AC7" box="[921,1073,656,677]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being less than the width of the puparium. In 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FC2BFD254B083AA7" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[985,1132,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamorum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FC2BFD254B083AA7" box="[985,1132,687,709]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">C. mamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is longer than the width of the puparium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A400C5F27FCC8FD764BF73B52" blockId="27.[826,1442,764,816]" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400C5F27FCC8FD764CF13B73" box="[826,917,764,785]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="294">Biology:</emphasis>
Reared from larvae found in a fallen, decaying bromeliad (
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400C5F27FC1BFC904BEC3B52" box="[1001,1160,794,816]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
